@disqus_Gwdmf3auhZ:disqus I perchance crossed this particular post and imagine my surprise! Firstly I'd like to congratulate you on your attempt at advocacy- very powerful language and I quite enjoy reading your post. I am also a student of this institution. Although I am unsure whether or not you are a high-school senior or a middle school senior, I do disapprove of the method in which the school handles things- especially their act of removing efficient teachers from the high school department to either to middle school or out of school. However forgive me for nitpicking but there are a few things I'd like to correct on the technology portion. Technology is very expensive, the newer versions of the iMac cost almost two grand each- multiply that by 30 for a room and 30 we have. They aren't the most recent- I believe those are the 2010 or '11 versions and this "Mac Room" is restricted to middle schoolers. The "Old Dell" laptops with XP are slowly being transitioned out and replaced with newer Lenovos with Win7. The majority of the school is already on Win7. 
The administration is a gathering of buffoons, no doubt about that. On the middle school section they have removed the class system and gave students are more personalized individual schedule. Sounds good? No. Students are in chaos. The idea of moving High-school teachers who are adept at teaching high-school students out of the school or to have them teach middle school students is preposterous! 
So yes, I do agree with some of what you have said and support your attempts. But be wary of exaggeration (so far as I know, people do not use drugs on the grounds). All in all, the school building itself is much better than some schools I have visited. Our classrooms are more modernized, not divided into A/B partitions and we have our own building.  The teachers, for the most part, are dedicated to their job and provide help if the student shows interest. In conclusion, was my experience at IN-Tech bad? No. Are we more technologically advanced than many NYC public schools? Yes. Do I disagree with the administration's recent actions? Definitely. Do I dislike certain staff? Who doesn't?! Is this school going to the pits? Maybe. Do I really care about what is to happen in the following years? ... Not really. Like you, Im outta here!!!!!
